        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 7:31PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pollard Flat, or 21 miles south of Mount Shasta, moving northeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sims, Vollmers, Pollard Flat, and Fisher.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
